body:
Why is the original Riven skin made in 2012, called &quot;Championship Riven 2016&quot;
while the new exclusive version made in 2016 is called &quot;Championship Riven&quot;?

Wouldn&#039;t it make vastly more sense for the one made in 2016, released in 2016 and will only ever available in 2016... be called &quot;Championship riven 2016&quot;?

While the original one made in 2012, and made available again _(no different to Haunting Noc and other skins who do not have a date added on the end of their name when re-released)_ keep the original name?

Not to mention that putting a date on the end of a skin name makes it look really bad, and seeming the original Championship Riven will be seen a lot more than the exclusive one, doesn&#039;t it also make more sense to keep the Original skin name looking tidy, and have the exclusive skin _(which already has a lot of messy extras like a border, crown and particle)_ have just 1 more extra, which is the date on the end of the skin?

{{sticker:zombie-brand-mindblown}}
